images.alt: A photorealistic cinematic movie poster for a spy action thriller titled “Man from D.R.A.G.O.N”. The main composition is a giant dragon head silhouette in double exposure, semi-transparent and designer-stylized, filling most of the poster. Inside the dragon’s head silhouette is the entire action collage: a handsome secret agent in a tuxedo aiming a silenced pistol, a glamorous blonde femme fatale holding a gun, masked tactical soldiers, a speedboat chase, a helicopter, a sports car exploding through the city, satellite dish, and multiple gunfight scenes.  All characters and vehicles are fully photorealistic, cinematic photography, not illustration. Real skin texture, real fabric, realistic lighting, realistic faces, shallow depth of field, movie-grade compositing.  The dragon itself is translucent and acts as a framing shape, its scales and eye subtly visible but the action scenes live inside the dragon silhouette using true double exposure compositing.  Background is a burning modern city at night, explosions, smoke, sparks, embers, volumetric fire and smoke, dramatic orange and blue cinematic color grading, HDR, ultra-detailed, IMAX-level sharpness.  Poster layout, vertical composition, blockbuster movie key art style, epic scale, high contrast, sharp focus, ultra high resolution, realistic lens effects, cinematic lighting, global illumination, film grain.  At the bottom: bold movie title text “MAN FROM D.R.A.G.O.N” in metallic glowing letters.
